-- Krispy Kreme net loss widens on higher charges, costs
-- 
-- Thu Sep 6, 2007 6:13pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/09/06/us-krispykreme-results-idUSWNAS363920070906

 

 (Reuters) - Krispy Kreme Doughnuts Inc ( KKD.N ) reported a wider second-quarter net loss on higher impairment charges and lease termination costs. 

 The doughnut-shop operator said net loss for the latest second quarter was $27 million, or 42 cents a share, compared with a net loss of $4.6 million, or 7 cents a share, in the year-ago period. Revenue dropped 7.5 percent to $104.1 million. Impairment charges and lease termination costs totaled $22.1 million in the second quarter this year, compared to $382,000 last year, the company said in a statement. (Reporting by Nachiket Kelkar in Bangalore)